const schemaFAQs = [
  {
    question: "How much does masonry waterproofing cost in Toronto?",
    answer: "Masonry waterproofing in Toronto costs $8-$20 per square foot depending on surface type and condition. Basic sealing costs $8-$12/sq ft, while comprehensive restoration with tuckpointing ranges from $17-$20/sq ft. Typical home projects cost $3,200-$13,000."
  },
  {
    question: "How long does masonry waterproofing take to complete?",
    answer: "Most masonry waterproofing projects take 3-7 days to complete. Surface preparation and sealing takes 2-4 days, while comprehensive restoration may require 5-7 days. Weather conditions affect outdoor curing times."
  },
  {
    question: "What are the benefits of masonry waterproofing?",
    answer: "Waterproofing prevents water damage, stops freeze-thaw cycling, prevents spalling and cracking, preserves structural integrity, improves curb appeal, and extends masonry lifespan. Our breathable sealers maintain natural moisture regulation."
  },
  {
    question: "When should I waterproof my masonry walls?",
    answer: "Waterproof masonry when you notice water stains, efflorescence (white deposits), cracking mortar joints, loose bricks, or interior dampness. Best applied in dry conditions between late spring and early fall for optimal curing."
